.PP
Cancel an internal timer in a generic FSM.

.PP
Cancels an internal timer referred by \fIRef\fR in the \fIgen_fsm\fR process that calls this function.

.PP
\fIRef\fR is a reference returned from \fIsend_event_after/2\fR or \fIstart_timer/2\fR.

.PP
If the timer has already timed out, but the event not yet been delivered, it is cancelled as if it had not timed out, so there is no false timer event after returning from this function.

.PP
Returns the remaining time in milliseconds until the timer would have expired if \fIRef\fR referred to an active timer, otherwise \fIfalse\fR.


