If \fB\fIFsmName = {via, Module, ViaName}\fR\fR, the \fIgen_fsm\fR process registers with the registry represented by \fIModule\fR.  The \fIModule\fR callback is to export the functions \fIregister_name/2\fR, \fIunregister_name/1\fR, \fIwhereis_name/1\fR, and \fIsend/2\fR, which are to behave like the corresponding functions in \fIglobal\fR. Thus, \fI{via, global, GlobalName}\fR is a valid reference.

.RE

.PP
