.br
.RS
.PP
Send a time-out event internally in a generic FSM.

.PP
Sends a time-out event internally in the \fIgen_fsm process\fR that calls this function after \fITime\fR milliseconds. Returns immediately a reference that can be used to cancel the timer using \fIcancel_timer/1\fR.

.PP
The \fIgen_fsm\fR process calls \fIModule:StateName/2\fR to handle the event, where \fI'StateName'\fR is the name of the current state of the \fIgen_fsm\fR process at the time the time-out message is delivered.

.PP
\fIMsg\fR is any term that is passed in the time-out message, \fI{timeout, Ref, Msg}\fR, as one of the arguments to \fIModule:StateName/2\fR.


